                            <comment id="12764529" author="drwoods" created="Mon, 12 Oct 2009 03:26:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a lot of code in Apache Geronimo and TranQL that you should be able to reuse for this.&lt;br/&gt;
Geronimo Transaction Manager -&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/geronimo/components/txmanager/branches/geronimo&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/geronimo/components/txmanager/branches/geronimo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
-txmanager-parent-2.1&lt;br/&gt;
TranQL DB connectors - &lt;a href=&quot;http://xircles.codehaus.org/projects/tranql&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://xircles.codehaus.org/projects/tranql&lt;/a&gt; -&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.codehaus.org/tranql/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://svn.codehaus.org/tranql/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12764720" author="ppoddar@apache.org" created="Mon, 12 Oct 2009 16:34:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The idea is to avoid bringing in a heavyweight container within OpenJPA test environment. &lt;br/&gt;
The contract between OpenJPA and a container is thin enough to provide a bare bone lightweight container implementation (which also, btw, many do). &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;But please give this one a try and see how it goes. It surely helps me to debug easily. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12764723" author="drwoods" created="Mon, 12 Oct 2009 16:43:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yep, wasn&apos;t suggesting that we use the whole Geronimo app server, but just the txmanager component (standalone JAR which Apache Aries is using for JTA support) and possibly the TranQL connectors, if we need to connect to databases other than Derby....&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
